  "notes2": {
    "id": "notes2",
    "y": 425,
    "width": 250,
    "z": 444,
    "movable": false,
    "css": {
      "font-size": "19px"
    },
    "text": "To change the color of the icon, use the 'show advanced options' button. This changes the icon property to an object and allows changes to the color and select other properties of the icon.",
    "x": 323
  },
  "notes3": {
    "id": "notes3",
    "x": 908,
    "y": 425,
    "width": 250,
    "z": 446,
    "movable": false,
    "css": {
      "font-size": "19px"
    },
    "text": "The advanced settings for icons allow using of variable values. This icon is set using a custom '${PROPERTY iconColor}`. The hover color can also be changed. This example also adjusts the stroke and fill colors separately."
  },
  "notes4": {
    "id": "notes4",
    "x": 1200,
    "y": 425,
    "width": 350,
    "z": 447,
    "movable": false,
    "css": {
      "font-size": "19px"
    },
    "text": "When multiple icons are on the same widget/face, the color of each icon, including its hover color, can be individually controlled through the icon object values."
  },
